# Verify Connector

> **Status: stub — implementation pending.** Contract only. Consolidates the
> verification steps across the source skills — the `[file-delivery]`
> log-read and count-match from `migrate-connector-to-arrow`, the
> `writing commit file` check from `add-measurement-feed-ingestion`, and the
> OAuth callback round-trip from `add-connector-oauth`.

## Purpose

Prove the deployed connector actually works before it carries customer
data: enqueue a delivery job, read the `[file-delivery]` logs, and confirm
delivered `total_rows` / `total_identifiers` match the expected baseline
exactly. Also exercises the OAuth callback round-trip and, when measurement
is in scope, the sample-file → `writing commit file` path.

Phase: **deploy/verify** (the final gate).

## Inputs (from connector-spec.yaml)

- `measurement.dataset_ids`, expected identifier counts / baseline.
- `auth` → the OAuth round-trip to exercise.
- `stages` → verify dev first, prod only after promotion.

## Outputs

- A verification report with a single go / no-go verdict.

## Human gates

- Runs **live jobs** — automatic in dev; **prod verification is confirmed
  first**.
- **Correctness rule:** a `total_rows` / `total_identifiers` mismatch is a
  no-go and a correctness regression, not a fix-forward. Blocks prod
  promotion.

